<TITLE> Sylhet transport strike suspended for 72hrs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Moulvibazar, May 9 (bdnews24.com)  Transport owners and workers in Sylhet division decided on Sunday to supended for 72 hours their indefinite strike, which had been called to seek government agreement to their five points of demand. Sylhet Bibhag Paribahan Malik Sramik Oikya Parisad had called the strike on Thursday evening demanding withdrawal of extortion cases against 31 transport owners and workers, including Syed Mofochchhil Ali, Syed Mofochchhil Ali, president of the Moulvibazar Minibus Owners Association among other demands. "The decision to halt the strike has been taken at the request of Bangladesh Road Transport Association's secretary general Enayet Ullah considering the sufferings of ordinary people," said Syed Mofochchhil Ali to bdnews24.com. Transport leaders warned that they would again go on strike again if their demands were not met within 72-hours. Although the Sylhet Bibhag Paribahan Malik Sramik Oikya Parisad had called for the strike to take place across Sylhet division, it had only been observed in Moulvibazar for three days since Thursday and two days in Hobiganj since Friday  but not in Sylhet or Sunamganj, bd
